<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA: TIPS; 
</P>
<P>
300 YARDS ACROSS THE SEA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
THIS JUST MIGHT be the best transportation bargain around. Far more scenic than 
a ride on the RTD, and much less crazy-making than getting a cab, it's the 
ferry ride between Balboa peninsula and Balboa Island. 
</P>
<P>
On the four-minute crossing, riders are treated to a stunning panorama of the 
Balboa waterfront. The Balboa Island Ferry runs daily, and tickets cost 65 
cents for car and driver, 25 cents for adults and 10 cents for kids. 
</P>
<P>
 Catch the ferry on Palm Street on the peninsula, and Agate Avenue on the 
island; (714) 673-1070. ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Balboa Island Robert Waddell 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
