<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRESIDENT BUSH RENEWS CHINA'S FAVORED-NATION TRADING STATUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding Bush's China policy: Whatever happened to "Let me walk a mile in my 
neighbors moccasins. . . ." Multiply the ills of the United States -- poverty, 
drugs, crime, health care, burdened legal system -- by four and place them in 
an environment of dwindling resources. The question is not what's good for 
America's future, but what will work for a country with 1 billion people and 
limited resources. 
</P>
<P>
K.R. JEWETT 
</P>
<P>
Marina del Rey 
</P>
</TEXT>
