<P>
MASSACHUSETTS; 
</P>
<P>
3 DEMOCRATS VIE TO SUCCEED DUKAKIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Atty. Gen. Francis X. Bellotti won the endorsement for governor at the 
state Democratic convention in Springfield, Mass. 
</P>
<P>
Boston University President John Silber, a maverick with growing popular 
support, won a spot in the primary. Lt. Gov. Evelyn Murphy also locked up a 
spot in September's primary with a second-place finish in voting by delegates. 
State Rep. John Flood was eliminated. The 5,000 delegates gave Gov. Michael S. 
Dukakis' farewell speech a standing ovation. The 1988 Democratic presidential 
candidate urged the party to stick by its agenda of affordable housing, 
environmental protection, universal health care and job training. 
</P>
</TEXT>
