<HEADLINE>
<P>
MADONNA: ONE STEP OVER THE LINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am 23 years old and have been a Madonna fan since she first arrived on the 
scene, but after having seen her recent "Blond Ambition" tour in Los Angeles, I 
am outraged. 
</P>
<P>
Madonna has always been known for her image of sexual promiscuity; however, in 
her current tour she has managed to step over the line between sexually 
suggestive and sexually explicit. 
</P>
<P>
I am concerned about the 10-year-old girls who idolize Madonna and use her as a 
role model. 
</P>
<P>
I feel that the public has a right to be forewarned of explicit sexual acts 
that take place at concerts such as Madonna's. It seems strange to me that you 
must be 17 to enter an R-rated movie, yet a child can walk into a Madonna 
concert and see her have simulated intercourse with her bed. 
</P>
<P>
MARY E. BEACH 
</P>
<P>
Studio City 
</P>
</TEXT>
