<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
* Robert Allen Skotheim, director of the Huntington Library, Art Collections 
and Botanical Gardens, has received honors from his alma mater, the University 
of Washington College of Arts and Sciences, and from Illinois Wesleyan 
University, where he delivered the commencement address May 12. 
</P>
<P>
The University of Washington College of Arts and Sciences presented Skotheim 
with its Distinguished Achievement Award for "his extraordinary accomplishments 
in professional life." Illinois Wesleyan awarded him an Honorary Doctorate of 
Humane Letters. 
</P>
