</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA060390-0094 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 228182 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 3, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
San Gabriel Valley; Part J; Page 2; Column 3 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
110 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ACCUSATIONS AGAINST GLENDORA'S MAYOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We believe a crime has been committed in Glendora but it was not our mayor, Bob 
Kuhn, who committed it. 
</P>
<P>
In our opinion, the crime that was committed was the false accusations against 
Bob Kuhn by one citizen in Glendora (Times, May 17). Because of the false 
accusations of this one citizen, Bob's name and reputation, which he has built 
over the last 25 years, was tarnished. 
</P>
<P>
Those of us who know Bob know that he would never do anything to jeopardize his 
reputation or his name. 
</P>
<P>
We hope that the person who was responsible for this fiasco realizes how 
foolish they look. No wonder they want to remain anonymous. 
</P>
<P>
JUDI and JERRY ROBINSON 
</P>
<P>
Glendora 
</P>
</TEXT>
