<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE IN THE NEWS: NURSING DIRECTOR WINS AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
* Marcia Grant, director of nursing research and education and an associate 
research scientist at City of Hope National Medical Center in Duarte, has 
received the ONS/Roche Distinguished Service Award from the Oncology Nursing 
Society. 
</P>
<P>
The $4,000 award acknowledges a member of the society who fosters high 
professional standards that improve the image and practice of oncology nursing. 
Grant's research focuses on nutrition and cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
