<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: 20-YEAR-OLD HELD IN DRIVE-BY SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 20-year-old Oxnard man was arrested early Saturday on suspicion of 
participating in a drive-by shooting, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses told police that a car with its lights switched off parked outside a 
house in the 400 block of Helsam Street in El Rio and fired into the living 
room window of a house, said Lt. Joe Funchess of the Ventura County Sheriff's 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
No one was hurt, Funchess said. 
</P>
<P>
Based on witnesses' accounts, sheriff's deputies arrested Fidel Melendez at his 
house about 6 a.m. Saturday, Funchess said. 
</P>
<P>
It was not known whether the incident was gang-related, Funchess said. 
</P>
<P>
Melendez was arrested on suspicion of shooting at an occupied dwelling and for 
several outstanding warrants, including failing to appear in court on a traffic 
citation, Funchess said. 
</P>
<P>
Melendez was being held Saturday at the Ventura County Jail in lieu of $5,500 
bail, Sheriff's Sgt. Bob Larson said. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
