<HEADLINE>
<P>
TAKIN ON THE CASH WINS KINDERGARTEN BY A LENGTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRAD McKINZIE, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Favored Takin On The Cash broke on the lead and was never really challenged in 
winning the $233,000 Kindergarten Stakes for 2-year-olds at Los Alamitos 
Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
With Danny Cardoza in the saddle for his third career Kindergarten victory, the 
Dash For Cash colt won by one length and was timed in 17.65 seconds for 350 
yards. 
</P>
<P>
Takin On The Cash has won three of his five career starts and earned $185,000. 
</P>
<P>
Takin On The Cash had been beaten in his Kindergarten trial on May 23, but 
trainer Caesar Dominguez was confident. 
</P>
<P>
Takin On The Cash paid $7.00, $4.00 and $2.80. 
</P>
<P>
Raised Toperfection, with thoroughbred jockey Gary Stevens in the saddle, 
finished eighth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA060390-0165 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 228413 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 3, 1990, Sunday, Bulldog Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 12; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
