<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A sailor was killed and at least 12 were injured when heavy seas caused chaos 
during one of Britain's biggest yacht races. 
</P>
<P>
Three yachts sank and several capsized in heavy swells in the English Channel 
off the Isle of Wight after 1,500 boats set off on the 52-mile 'Round the 
Island Race. Rescue officials said an unidentified sailor died when he was hit 
by a boom. Two sailors suffered broken arms when their yachts collided and 
another had a heart attack, officials said. 
</P>
