</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
El Toro 1, Don Lugo 0 -- Jamie Smith drove in the game's only run in the bottom 
of the eighth inning, giving El Toro the Southern Section 3-A softball 
championship. 
</P>
<P>
With two outs, Smith beat the throw from Chino Don Lugo shortstop Michelle 
Macias, allowing Corrie Yauney to score a run that was set up by several 
umpiring calls questioned by Don Lugo Coach Ray Sheffield. 
</P>
<P>
Sheffield argued that Kymm Maniscalco, who began the decisive eighth inning 
with an infield single, was out at first base by a full step. Yauney then 
forced Maniscalco at second base. Sheffield again argued when Karie Yoshioka 
was called safe on an infield single on which Yauney went to third during the 
argument. 
</P>
<P>
Paige Lauby was the winning pitcher, giving up four hits, striking out 12 and 
walking one. Agoura 4, Paraclete 0 -- Michelle Ray and Kim Bunch singled and 
scored in a three-run third inning that powered the Chargers (23-5) to the 
Southern Section Division 1-A championship. 
</P>
