<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: LINDEMANN LEADS DUNCAN BY TWO SHOTS IN AMATEUR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Richard Lindemann shot a three-under-par 69 on the South Course at Torrey Pines 
Saturday to take a two-stroke lead over three-time defending champion Pat 
Duncan after one round of the 58th San Diego Men's Amateur Golf Championships. 
</P>
<P>
Ken Earle shot a 72, and four were tied at 74. 
</P>
<P>
David Sittner's net 65 on the North Course led the first flight, and Cy Peacher 
and Herb Schamp had 64s to share the second flight lead. 
</P>
<P>
At Balboa Park, D.E. Kay led the third flight with 65, while three -- Jose 
Salazar, Vince Martinez Sr. and Michael Carlson -- were tied for first at 66 in 
the fourth flight. 
</P>
<P>
SAILING 
</P>
<P>
The Long Beach Yacht Club's Camouflage, skippered by Alvin Schultz, won its 
second consecutive race and was the overall leader after two days of the San 
Diego Yacht Club's Lipton Cup Regatta. 
</P>
<P>
On corrected time, Camouflage won by just four seconds over Cadenza, skippered 
by Carl Eichenlaub of the San Diego Yacht Club. Quintessence of the Santa 
Barbara Yacht Club, skippered by Donald Hughes, was third. 
</P>
<P>
With the final race today, Camouflage leads the overall standings with 1.5 
points to 5 for Quintessence and 6 for Cadenza. 
</P>
<P>
SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
Mark Semioli scored past goalie Anton Nistle with less than four minutes left 
to give the San Francisco Bay Blackhawks a 1-0 victory over the Nomads at 
Southwestern College. 
</P>
<P>
The loss dropped the Nomads to 4-6 in the Western Soccer League. League-leading 
San Francisco is 7-1. 
</P>
<P>
TRACK AND FIELD 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego will hold two Twilight All-Comers Track and Field meets this 
Friday and Friday, June 22, at the UCSD track. The meets begin at 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Participants must purchase event stickers for $2 for each event and must enter 
at least 20 minutes before the event begins. 
</P>
