<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAIL INITIATIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Measure A, the so-called Centralized Jail Initiative, would mandate that all 
new jails be built in the county seat, Santa Ana. It is questionable that this 
measure, if passed, would withstand a legal challenge. 
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless it poses a serious threat to efforts that have already been made 
to plan a remote jail site. 
</P>
<P>
We're all concerned about crime, and we all want to ensure that criminals are 
expeditiously tried, convicted and incarcerated. Measure A proponents would 
like all this to take place in Santa Ana. Let's be reasonable; Santa Ana simply 
isn't the place for all jails. The city is densely populated and has the most 
rapidly growing school population in the county. Both are adequate reasons to 
disqualify Santa Ana as a potential site. 
</P>
<P>
Please vote no on Measure A and make it clear to the County Board of 
Supervisors and Measure A proponents that a remote jail site is the appropriate 
solution to a pressing need. 
</P>
<P>
KEITH SWAYNE 
</P>
<P>
