<DOCID> 228851 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 3, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 4; Column 5; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
276 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MONEY FUND YIELDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Highest seven-day compound yields for period ended May 29. Yields represent 
compounded rate of return to shareholders for past seven days. 
</P>
<P>
Past returns are not necessarily indicative of future yields. Investment 
quality and maturity may vary among funds. 
</P>
<P>
GOVERNMENT ONLY 
</P>
<P>
Average: 7.75% 
</P>
