<HEADLINE>
<P>
REMODELING PAYMENTS REGULATED IN STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In California, home improvement payments -- including down payments paid to the 
contractor by the owner -- are regulated by law, according to the National 
Assn. of the Remodeling Industry. 
</P>
<P>
Section 7159 of the California contractors' license law provides when the 
payment schedule calls for a down payment that the down payment be no more than 
$1,000 or 10% of the contract price, whichever is less. Exceptions are made for 
deposits for one-of-a-kind or special-ordered products. 
</P>
<P>
The Southern California chapter of the national remodeling trade association 
cautions against consumers being "lured into giving large deposits in exchange 
for big discounts" on their remodeling projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
